The paper deals with linear regression and matrix estimation, which are core topics in machine learning and data science. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves sampling techniques and optimization, which are relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The use of matrix expectations and covariance matrices suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as possible sub-categories as well.
